Aren't you worried you're making
French toast on oatmeal day?

22
00:01:18,690 --> 00:01:21,257
Ah, well, what's this?
A pot of oatmeal?

23
00:01:21,258 --> 00:01:25,293
Or, thanks to you, what
I will now call "gloatmeal."

24
00:01:25,296 --> 00:01:28,364
Oh, I don't want credit
for that.

25
00:01:29,365 --> 00:01:31,166
Oh, Dr. and Mrs. Hofstadter,

26
00:01:31,168 --> 00:01:33,335
lovely to see you
this fine morning.

27
00:01:33,338 --> 00:01:34,403
You're in a good mood.

28
00:01:34,404 --> 00:01:35,671
Yeah, I am indeed.

29
00:01:35,672 --> 00:01:37,139
I have decided,

30
00:01:37,142 --> 00:01:39,174
instead of wallowing
in sadness about Amy,

31
00:01:39,177 --> 00:01:42,445
it is time that I find myself
a new female companion.

32
00:01:42,446 --> 00:01:43,645
Oh. Good for you.

33
00:01:43,648 --> 00:01:45,148
What brought this on?

34
00:01:45,150 --> 00:01:47,517
I realized something—
when Amy was in my life,

35
00:01:47,519 --> 00:01:49,886
I was hyper-focused on my work
and ignored her.

36
00:01:49,888 --> 00:01:51,053
And you don't want

37
00:01:51,055 --> 00:01:53,121
to make the same mistake
with the next woman.

38
00:01:53,124 --> 00:01:55,725
No, I need a new woman
in my life to ignore

39
00:01:55,726 --> 00:01:58,026
so I can hyper-focus
on my work again.

40
00:01:58,029 --> 00:02:00,296
Hey, I made
French toast sticks.

41
00:02:00,297 --> 00:02:01,764
On oatmeal day?

42
00:02:01,766 --> 00:02:04,199
Ah, I also made oatmeal.
Ooh,

43
00:02:04,201 --> 00:02:07,203
that's a lot of carbohydrates
for a man on the prowl.

44
00:02:07,204 --> 00:02:09,272
You know what?
You eat it; you're married—

45
00:02:09,274 --> 00:02:11,641
it doesn't matter
what you look like.

46
00:02:12,842 --> 00:02:16,745
Don't take advice from a man
who threw his shoe at a crow.

